#  Go Network Programming

This repository contains educational examples and small projects focused on **network programming with Go**.  
It explores how Go’s standard `net` package can be used to build, analyze, and understand real-world network communication systems.

Make sure you have **Go 1.20 or newer** installed.


# References
The concepts and examples in this repository are inspired by the following resources:
Jan Newmarch, Ronald Petty – “Network Programming with Go”
Springer, 2021 — ISBN 978-1-4842-6874-8
A comprehensive guide to Go’s networking capabilities.

The Go Programming Language Documentation

https://pkg.go.dev/net

https://go.dev/doc/effective_go

RFC Standards
RFC 791 – Internet Protocol (IP)
RFC 793 – Transmission Control Protocol (TCP)
RFC 867 – Daytime Protocol

Go Blog – Concurrency and Networking Patterns
https://blog.golang.org/pipelines